                            <comment id="14707367" author="larsgeorge" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2015 19:55:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmmm, thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ndimiduk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ndimiduk&quot;&gt;Nick Dimiduk&lt;/a&gt;, I looked there and was not able to get done what I tried. I am at a loss now to replicate. Let me check tomorrow and if I cannot redo I will close this issue. Sorry for the (possible) noise.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15662626" author="anoop.hbase" created="Mon, 14 Nov 2016 03:15:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In CellUtil, which is public, we have diff versions of createCell APIs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;public static Cell createCell(final byte [] row, final byte [] family, final byte [] qualifier) &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here we don&apos;t have value to be passed.  We should be having an overloaded API which takes value byte[] also..  Seems that is what Lars looking for.&lt;br/&gt;
Should be a simple API. I can give a quick patch.  Or u r working on it in some other way &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=saint.ack%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;saint.ack@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Stack&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
